  <h2>Secrets Management</h2>

  <p>
    Portefaix uses <a href="https://github.com/getsops/sops" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SOPS</a>
    (Secrets OPerationS) to encrypt secrets before committing them to Git. Decryption keys are managed
    via cloud KMS (GCP KMS, AWS KMS) or PGP, so secrets are safe at rest in the repository while
    being automatically decrypted during reconciliation.
  </p>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <p>
      <strong>Key insight:</strong> Never commit unencrypted secrets to Git — even in a private repository.
      SOPS encrypts values while preserving the YAML/JSON structure, making diffs readable.
    </p>
  </div>
